    "body": "### Problem\n\nI've been using #29225 autocmd since many months ago and it worked pretty good in my config. I was happy when it was closed with #32820 so I remove it for more robust implementation. But when trying it out I don't get the same results as in the mentioned autocmd.\n\nThese are the docs I get with builtin:\n\n<img width=\"937\" height=\"120\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cf6f9340-6ae7-48e7-b4fb-57d358330581\" />\n\n\nThis is what I get with the autocmd:\n\n<img width=\"1431\" height=\"376\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/06fe71ab-5174-4943-b850-355bbfecd50e\" />\n\nBoth examples are with the same lua_ls configuration, adding vimruntime to its library (check below). With the builtin-documentation-config I get documentation when using `K`, so the ls is picking it.\n\nI didn't find any other issue related to this specifically, so I documented it here.\n\n<details>\n<summary>Tested config (builtin-documentation-config has the `if client:supports_method(\"completionItem/resolve\") then` if commented out)</summary>\n\n```lua\nvim.o.completeopt = \"menuone,popup,noselect,fuzzy\"\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"LspAttach\", {\n\tgroup = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup(\"lsp-attach\", { clear = true }),\n\tcallback = function(args)\n\t\tlocal client_id = args.data.client_id\n\t\tlocal buf = args.buf\n\t\tlocal client = assert(vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(client_id))\n\n\t\tif client:supports_method(\"completionItem/resolve\") then\n\t\t\t---@param items table<integer, { err: (lsp.ResponseError)?, result: any, context: lsp.HandlerContext }>\n\t\t\tlocal function get_docs(items)\n\t\t\t\tfor _, item in ipairs(items) do\n\t\t\t\t\tif item.result.documentation then\n\t\t\t\t\t\treturn item.result.documentation\n\t\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\tend\n\n\t\t\tlocal cancel_prev = function() end\n\t\t\tvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"CompleteChanged\", {\n\t\t\t\tbuffer = buf,\n\t\t\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\t\t\tcancel_prev()\n\t\t\t\t\tlocal info = vim.fn.complete_info({ \"selected\" })\n\t\t\t\t\tlocal completionItem =\n\t\t\t\t\t\tvim.tbl_get(vim.v.completed_item, \"user_data\", \"nvim\", \"lsp\", \"completion_item\")\n\t\t\t\t\tif nil == completionItem then\n\t\t\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t\t\tcancel_prev = vim.lsp.buf_request_all(\n\t\t\t\t\t\tbuf,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tvim.lsp.protocol.Methods.completionItem_resolve,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tcompletionItem,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tfunction(items, _)\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tif not items or #items == 0 then\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tlocal docs = get_docs(items)\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tif docs then\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tlocal win = vim.api.nvim__complete_set(info[\"selected\"], { info = docs.value })\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tif win.winid and vim.api.nvim_win_is_valid(win.winid) then\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tvim.treesitter.start(win.bufnr, docs.kind)\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tvim.wo[win.winid].conceallevel = 3\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\t\t\t)\n\t\t\t\tend,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\tend\n\n\t\tvim.lsp.completion.enable(true, client_id, buf, {})\n\n\t\tvim.keymap.set(\"i\", \"<C-n>\", function()\n\t\t\tvim.lsp.completion.get()\n\t\tend)\n\tend,\n})\n\nvim.lsp.config(\"lua_ls\", {\n\tcmd = { \"lua-language-server\" },\n\tfiletypes = { \"lua\" },\n\troot_markers = {\n\t\t\".luarc.json\",\n\t\t\".luarc.jsonc\",\n\t\t\".luacheckrc\",\n\t\t\".stylua.toml\",\n\t\t\"stylua.toml\",\n\t\t\".git\",\n\t},\n\tlog_level = vim.lsp.protocol.MessageType.Warning,\n\tsettings = {\n\t\tLua = {\n\t\t\tcodeLens = { enable = true },\n\t\t\tformat = { enable = false },\n\t\t\tcompletion = { callSnippet = \"Replace\" },\n\t\t\thint = { enable = true, arrayIndex = \"Disable\" },\n\t\t\ttelemetry = { enable = false },\n\t\t\truntime = { version = \"LuaJIT\" },\n\t\t\tworkspace = {\n\t\t\t\tcheckThirdParty = false,\n\t\t\t\tlibrary = {\n\t\t\t\t\tvim.env.VIMRUNTIME,\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t},\n\t},\n})\n\nvim.lsp.enable(\"lua_ls\")\n```\n</details>\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCompletion documentation should show documentation, not only signatures, snippets, etc.",
